We recommended that the Management:

a. 	direct the Municipal Treasurer to enforce remedies on collections of delinquent real property taxes as prescribed in Section 256 to 260 of the Local Government Code and/or formulate strategies and conduct tax campaigns;

b. 	instruct the Municipal Assessor to submit an updated Assessment Roll to the Municipal Treasurer’s Office,  to serve as their guide in the collection of RPT,  to keep their records updated and to monitor status of collection of current and delinquent taxpayers.

1. Send demand letters to barangays for the immediate liquidation of the funds transferred to them;

2. Stop granting to barangays with unliquidated balances to the municipality; and

3. Revise the MOA to be used for the future fund transfers to barangays indicating there in the fixed date/period when to properly liquidate the funds transferred by the municipality.

